1) What is a server?
   	- Computer system that provide services to client over the internet. Servies such as web hoisting, database management, email servies etc
2) What is the role of the domain name
	- Domain name helps human remember name of a resources such as website since it might be difficult to memorize the IP addresses.

3) What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
	- The type of DNS record is A record. A record maps the domain name with the IP address (www.foobar.com - 8.8.8.8)

4) What is the role of the web server?
	- receives HTTP request and reponds with a HTTP request.
	- Software that delivers webpages and other web content over the internet

5) What is the role of the application server?
	- serves business logic to application programs.

6) What is the role of the database?
	- store organized information or data that is retrieved when application  server makes the request to database server

7) What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
	- Internet
